.TH PKGMAN-INFO 8 "PKGMAN-#VERSION# Manual"

.SH NAME
pkgman-info \- print package info

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pkgman info
.BI [-v|-vv] \ PKG

.SH DESCRIPTION
Print available info for a package.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v , \-vv
Print also the README file if exists.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PAGER
If the package' source directory has a README file, and the
.B \-v
or
.B \-vv
option is set to print it, then \fBpkgman\fR will try to open it
using a \fBPAGER\fR.
If \fBPAGER\fR is unset, then \fBpkgman\fR prints the README to stdout. 
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 if success, 255 otherwise.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pkgman-readme (8),\  pkgman-readme (5)

